<div style="border: 1px solid #D00; background: #ddeeff; color: black; padding: .1em; text-align: center; letter-spacing: 2px; word-spacing:3px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 100%; margin-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: none;"><i>Where in Bangladesh...</i></div>
<div style="display: block; border: 1px solid #D00; vertical-align: top; background: white; color: black; margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 1em; margin-top: 0em; padding-top: .3em;">
<p><span style="text-align: right; float:right; margin:-.9em -.9em .3em .3em; padding: -.9em -.9em .3em .3em;"><small class="editlink noprint plainlinksneverexpand"><a class="external text" href="../../w/index-title=Portal_Bangladesh_Where_in_Bangladesh&action=edit.php.html">edit</a></small></span></p>
<p><br /></p>
<table cellspacing="3" style="text-align: center; float: center;">
<tr>
<td align="left" colspan="3"><b><a href="Wari-Bateshwar_ruins" title="Wari-Bateshwar ruins">Wari-Bateshwar</a></b> is the site of an ancient fort city dating back to 450 BC. This 2,500 years old site is a significant archaeological discovery that challenges the earlier notions about the existence of early urban civilisation in <a href="Bangladesh" title="Bangladesh">Bangladesh</a>. Do you know where in Bangladesh is <b>Wari-Bateshwar ruins</b>?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center" colspan="3">
<div style="align: center; float: center; width:240px; background:transparent">
<div style="position:relative; align: center; float: center; width:180px"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Loc_bangladesh2.svg" class="image"><img alt="Loc bangladesh2.svg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Loc_bangladesh2.svg/180px-Loc_bangladesh2.svg.png" width="180" height="251" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Loc_bangladesh2.svg/270px-Loc_bangladesh2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Loc_bangladesh2.svg/360px-Loc_bangladesh2.svg.png 2x" /></a><br />
<div style="position:absolute;z-index:200; top:41.7%; left:61.3%; height:0; width:0; margin:0; padding:0;">
<div style="position:relative; top:-4px; left:-4px; width:8px; text-align:center; z-index:201"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Red_pog.svg" class="image"><img alt="Red pog.svg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0c/Red_pog.svg/5px-Red_pog.svg.png" width="5" height="5" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0c/Red_pog.svg/8px-Red_pog.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0c/Red_pog.svg/10px-Red_pog.svg.png 2x" /></a></div>
<div style="font-size:90%; line-height:110%; position:relative; top:-1.5em; left:-6.5em; width:6em; text-align:right; z-index:202;"><span style="padding:1px;background:none">Wari-Bateshwar ruins</span></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left" colspan="3">The site is about 75km from <a href="Dhaka" title="Dhaka">Dhaka</a> situated near the Wari and Bateshwar villages in the Belabo <a href="Upazila" title="Upazila" class="mw-redirect">Upazila</a> of <a href="Narsingdi_District" title="Narsingdi District">Narsingdi District</a> under <a href="Dhaka_Division" title="Dhaka Division">Dhaka Division</a> in the north-eastern part of <a href="Bangladesh" title="Bangladesh">Bangladesh</a>.</td>
</tr>
</table>
