<div style="display: block; border: 1px solid #D00; vertical-align: top; background: white; color: black; margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 1em; margin-top: 0em; padding-top: .3em;">
<p><span style="text-align: right; float:right; margin:-.9em -.9em .3em .3em; padding: -.9em -.9em .3em .3em;"><small class="editlink noprint plainlinksneverexpand"><a class="external text" href="../../w/index-title=Portal_Bangladesh_Selected_picture&action=edit.php.html">edit</a></small></span></p>
<table cellspacing="3" style="text-align: center; float: center;">
<tr>
<td colspan="2" align="center">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Asian_Pied_Starling_(Sturnus_contra)_on_Kapok_(Ceiba_pentandra)_in_Kolkata_W_IMG_4513.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Asian Pied Starling (Sturnus contra) on Kapok (Ceiba pentandra) in Kolkata W IMG 4513.jpg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Asian_Pied_Starling_(Sturnus_contra)_on_Kapok_(Ceiba_pentandra)_in_Kolkata_W_IMG_4513.jpg/300px-Asian_Pied_Starling_(Sturnus_contra)_on_Kapok_(Ceiba_pentandra)_in_Kolkata_W_IMG_4513.jpg" width="300" height="283" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Asian_Pied_Starling_%28Sturnus_contra%29_on_Kapok_%28Ceiba_pentandra%29_in_Kolkata_W_IMG_4513.jpg/450px-Asian_Pied_Starling_%28Sturnus_contra%29_on_Kapok_%28Ceiba_pentandra%29_in_Kolkata_W_IMG_4513.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Asian_Pied_Starling_%28Sturnus_contra%29_on_Kapok_%28Ceiba_pentandra%29_in_Kolkata_W_IMG_4513.jpg/600px-Asian_Pied_Starling_%28Sturnus_contra%29_on_Kapok_%28Ceiba_pentandra%29_in_Kolkata_W_IMG_4513.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><b><a href="Asian_Pied_Starling" title="Asian Pied Starling" class="mw-redirect">Asian Pied Starling</a></b> (Sturnus contra) is one of the 12 species of <a href="Sturnidae" title="Sturnidae" class="mw-redirect">sturnidae</a> family birds that are resident in <a href="Bangladesh" title="Bangladesh">Bangladesh</a>. Locally known as <i>Myna</i> (<a href="Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a>: <span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">ময়না</span>) or <i>Shalik</i> (<a href="Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a>: <span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">শালিক</span> ), these birds build their nests in holes or cavities in trees or buildings, or large globular structures of straw, twigs, etc. in trees.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><small>Photo credit: <a class="external text" href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:J.M.Garg">J.M.Garg</a></small><br />
<div style="float: right;"></div>
</td>
</tr>
